      "topFalsePositivePatterns": [
        "ramp→sink combinatorial blowup: every mana rock/dork is edged to every X-spell or mana-using card, producing a near-complete bipartite fan that is present in essentially every Commander deck and is not deck-specific synergy. It is the single most frequently-cited false positive and dominates edge counts (e.g. 198 of 358 edges in Eldrazi Incursion, 605 family-instances in Divine Convocation, 170 in Token Triumph, 126 in Hail Caesar).",
        "lord→tribe fires without checking the lord's actual buff condition or whether the card is a lord at all: legendary-only anthems (Bastion Protector), single-type lords (Cat/Dog/Knight/Spirit lords), global combat anthems (Beastmaster Ascension, Skyhunter Strike Force), and token-making planeswalkers/creatures (Elspeth Sun's Champion, Vivien Reid, Esika) get wired to the entire creature base. Often the deck's highest-degree false hub.",
        "Undirected 'graveyard' mega-clique: every card that touches the yard (self-mill cantrips, recursion, reanimation, graveyard-hate) is edged to every other, conflating fuel↔fuel, enabler↔payoff, and incidental text. Inflates edge count massively (702 in Sultai Arisen, 485/530 in Revenant Recon, 245 in Death Toll, 215 in Desert Bloom) while hiding the real mill→reanimate / mill→size-payoff direction."
      ]
    }
